article.headline: Texas Southern 88, Prairie View 72
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Christopher Moore shot 9-of-11 for 25 points, and Sean Walker added 17 points in Texas Southern's 88-72 win over Prairie View A&M on Saturday night. Courtenay Brown had 15 points, all on 3-pointers, for Texas Southern (3-12, 1-2, Southwestern Athletic). Matthew Bell matched Moore for a team-high nine rebounds. The Tigers hit 47 percent of their shots. Anthony Oha scored a team-high 12 points, and Dominique Sharpe and Oscar Thompson added 11 points apiece for Prairie View (3-10, 0-3). Sharpe had nine rebounds for the Panthers, which trailed 48-42 at the half. Prairie View hit about 38 percent of its shots.
